==English==
[[Category:Pedophilia]]
[[Category:English nouns]]
===Etymology===
From Greek [[παιδοφιλια]] ''(paidophilia)'' < παις ''(pais)'' "boy, child" and φιλια ''(philia)'' "friendship"

====Pronunciation====
*{{AHD|/pĕd'ə-fīl'/}}
*{{IPA|/pidəfajl/}}

===Alternative spellings===
*[[pedophile]]
*[[pædophile]]

===Noun===
'''paedophile'''
# an adult who is sexually attracted primarily to prepubescent children
# micael jackson
====Usage notes====
*The term ''paedophile'' is sometimes used informally, and incorrectly, to describe adults who engage in sexual activity with children (this is properly termed ''[[child molester]]'').
*The term ''paedophile'' has also been used as a [[slur]] to refer to adults in relationships with adolescents, properly termed ''[[paederast]]''.

